LineNo: 10197030,

Player_Romus_Italic: I made my way to the stone arch and...
en


I made my way to the stone arch and sat down next to my daughter.

LineNo: 10197036,

Player_Romus_Italic: I made my way to the stone arch and...
Menu Text en


Talk to Vina.

LineNo: 10197138,

Estela Toras: I'm surprised you haven't died of...
en


"I'm surprised you haven't died of boredom yet."

LineNo: 10197256,

Player_Romus: Got a cigarette?
en


"Got a cigarette?"

LineNo: 10197358,

Player_Romus: I'm discussing the fate of the cou...
en


"I'm discussing the fate of the country. How could I be bored?"

LineNo: 10197460,

Player_Romus: It's only a matter of time.
en


"It's only a matter of time."

LineNo: 10197562,

Estela Toras: Is the Grand Wiseman Nurist?
en


"Is the Grand Wiseman Nurist?"

LineNo: 10197664,

Narrator: She lit two cigarettes and handed o...
en


She lit two cigarettes and handed one to me.

LineNo: 10197766,

Estela Toras: The fate of the country depends on...
en


"The fate of the country depends on tax rates and trade agreements, I see. Wake me when there's a war."

LineNo: 10197868,

Estela Toras: If your uncle was any more pleased...
en


"If your uncle was any more pleased with the sound of his own voice, he'd be a parakeet."

LineNo: 10197970,

Estela Toras: Seriously, I hope you're faring we...
en


"Seriously, I hope you're faring well thus far."

LineNo: 10198096,

Player_Romus: Do you trust Hugo?
en


"Do you trust Hugo?"

LineNo: 10198198,

Player_Romus: Did you know about the Golden Guar...
en


"Did you know about the Golden Guard?"

LineNo: 10198300,

Player_Romus: It's a lot to take in.
en


"It's a lot to take in."

LineNo: 10198402,

Estela Toras: You're asking the wrong person. Do...
en


"You're asking the wrong person. Don't forget, he positively loathes me."

LineNo: 10198504,

Estela Toras: Of course, darling. They're a litt...
en


"Of course, darling. They're a little unnerving at first, but that Titus fellow would take a bullet for you."

LineNo: 10198606,

Narrator: She stormed off, leaving me to my o...
en


She stormed off, leaving me to my own thoughts. Before I knew it, it was time for the council meeting.

LineNo: 10198708,

Player_Romus: Good to see you outside of the cou...
en


"Good to see you outside of the council chambers. Do you have any questions about the past few meetings?"

LineNo: 10198810,

Estela Toras: With that said, he was nothing but...
en


"With that said, he was nothing but loyal to your father. And that loyalty extends to anyone with the last name Toras, personal squabbles aside."

LineNo: 10198920,

Estela Toras: Even more so for Vina, I imagine.
en


"Even more so for Vina, I imagine."

LineNo: 10199038,

Estela Toras: Now picture your daughter having t...
en


"Now picture your daughter having to fill her head with that drivel. Aren't you glad you kept her off the Council?"

LineNo: 10199426,

Player_Romus: I'm relieved to hear that.
en


"I'm relieved to hear that."

LineNo: 10199528,

Player_Romus: I wouldn't be so sure, myself.
en


"I wouldn't be so sure, myself."

LineNo: 10199630,

Player_Romus: I can tell she's struggling, but s...
en


"I can tell she's struggling, but she'll learn."

LineNo: 10199732,

Player_Romus: I don't know. Maybe it would have...
en


"I don't know. Maybe it would have been a valuable experience."

LineNo: 10199834,

Player_Romus: I bet you're wishing you'd never a...
en


"I bet you're wishing you'd never asked to come to my meetings, right?"

LineNo: 10199936,

Vina Toras: What are you talking about? It's b...
en


"What are you talking about? It's been fascinating!"

LineNo: 10200038,

Narrator: To my left, I saw Vina reading a bo...
en


To my left, I saw Vina reading a book on a bench beneath a decorative stone arch. In the date palm grove to my right, I caught a glimpse of my mother.

LineNo: 10200148,

Player_Romus: Yes, she's lucky not to have to de...
en


"Yes, she's lucky not to have to deal with it all."

LineNo: 10200250,

Player_Romus: Sorry if Uncle Hugo made you feel...
en


"Sorry if Uncle Hugo made you feel uncomfortable the other day."

LineNo: 10200352,

Player_Romus: Yes, I'm starting to regret giving...
en


"Yes, I'm starting to regret giving in to her."

LineNo: 10200454,

Player_Romus: What's that you've been reading?
en


"What's that you've been reading?"

LineNo: 10200562,

Estela Toras: Let's hope it never comes to that....
en


"Let's hope it never comes to that. It'd be a waste of a spectacular torso."

LineNo: 10200672,

Player_Romus: We're sitting on so much money. Wh...
en


"We're sitting on so much money. Why didn't Father do anything with it?"

LineNo: 10200774,

Player_Romus: Better his than mine.
en


"Better his than mine."

LineNo: 10200876,

Player_Romus: Spectacular? I hadn't noticed.
en


"Spectacular? I hadn't noticed."

LineNo: 10200978,

Estela Toras: He was paralyzed at the end. By th...
en


"He was paralyzed at the end. By the weight of all the decisions he had made, and the fear of making a faulty one."

LineNo: 10201080,

Estela Toras: Nearly losing you had a momentous...
en


"Nearly losing you had a momentous effect on him. On us both."

LineNo: 10201198,

Narrator: A bell chimed in the distance. It w...
en


A bell chimed in the distance. It was time for the meeting to begin.

LineNo: 10201300,

Player_Romus: I *did* lose my wife. I managed to...
en


"I *did* lose my wife. I managed to keep myself together."

LineNo: 10201402,

Player_Romus: I can respect that. I haven't been...
en


"I can respect that. I haven't been the same since losing Lena."

LineNo: 10201504,

Player_Romus: And now I've got to pick up all of...
en


"And now I've got to pick up all of his slack."

LineNo: 10201606,

Player_Romus: She's keeping up just fine.
en


"She's keeping up just fine."

LineNo: 10201708,

Player_Romus: Listen, I'll give the book back to...
en


"Listen, I'll give the book back to you. But don't let anyone else catch you reading it."

LineNo: 10201810,

Player_Romus_Italic: I snatched the book out of Vina's b...
en


I snatched the book out of Vina's bag.

LineNo: 10201816,

Player_Romus_Italic: I snatched the book out of Vina's b...
Menu Text en


Take the book and look at it.

LineNo: 10201918,

Player_Romus_Italic: I made my way to the palm grove and...
en


I made my way to the palm grove and tapped my mother on the shoulder.

LineNo: 10201924,

Player_Romus_Italic: I made my way to the palm grove and...
Menu Text en


Talk to your mother.

LineNo: 10202026,

Vina Toras: That's okay. I know he means well.
en


"That's okay. I know he means well."

LineNo: 10202406,

Narrator: She hurriedly shoved the book she w...
en


She hurriedly shoved the book she was reading into her handbag. On the cover were the words "Ce Faximi" -- "What Are We To Do?" in Rizian.

LineNo: 10202524,

Vina Toras: Oh! Greetings, Father.
en


"Oh! Greetings, Father."

LineNo: 10202626,

Player_Romus: Show me that book. Now.
en


"Show me that book. Now."

LineNo: 10202734,

Narrator: Vina sheepishly fished the book out...
en


Vina sheepishly fished the book out of her bag and handed it to me.

LineNo: 10202836,

Narrator: I took a closer look at the cover....
en


I took a closer look at the cover. Beneath the title were the words, "A Collection of Proposals by L. Chavatangakwunua."

LineNo: 10202962,

Player_Romus: The uprising didn't succeed becaus...
en


"The uprising didn't succeed because the Rizian people knew what was good for them. A strong leader and strong laws."

LineNo: 10203064,

Vina Toras: No! You can't do that!
en


"No! You can't do that!"

LineNo: 10203166,

Player_Romus: Chava-what?
en


"Chava-what?"

LineNo: 10203268,

Player_Romus: This had better not be what I thin...
en


"This had better not be what I think it is."

LineNo: 10203370,

Narrator: She bit her lip nervously.
en


She bit her lip nervously.

LineNo: 10203496,

Player_Romus: It failed because it lacked cohesi...
en


"It failed because it lacked cohesion. Every faction was fighting for something different."

LineNo: 10203598,

Vina Toras: Look at what he writes here. True...
en


"Look at what he writes here. True systemic change can only be accomplished with the wholehearted support of the working class."

LineNo: 10203700,

Player_Romus: Workers did join the protests. But...
en


"Workers did join the protests. But yes, the initial spark came from naval officers."

LineNo: 10203802,

Player_Romus: You don't need to bother with this...
en


"You don't need to bother with this. You're a princess, not an intellectual."

LineNo: 10203904,

Player_Romus: Enroll in etiquette classes. Learn...
en


"Enroll in etiquette classes. Learn how to bake. The possibilities are endless."

LineNo: 10204006,

Vina Toras: You can't control what I read, you...
en


"You can't control what I read, you know. I'm a grown woman."

LineNo: 10204108,

Player_Romus: All right. But don't let anyone el...
en


"All right. But don't let anyone else catch you reading it."

LineNo: 10204210,

Player_Romus: It would be easier if I knew whom...
en


"It would be easier if I knew whom I could trust."

LineNo: 10204408,

Vina Toras: It's not as extreme as his later w...
en


"It's not as extreme as his later work. He wrote it right before changing his last name to Malenyev."

LineNo: 10204510,

Vina Toras: He changed it to Malenyev right af...
en


"He changed it to Malenyev right after this was published."

LineNo: 10204612,

Player_Romus: This is dangerous propaganda, Vina...
en


"This is dangerous propaganda, Vina. Don't you realize Malenyev and his followers hate people like you and me?"

LineNo: 10204714,

Vina Toras: Isn't that why it's important to k...
en


"Isn't that why it's important to know how they think?"

LineNo: 10204816,

Player_Romus: You know, I've always been curious...
en


"You know, I've always been curious about Malenyevism. Do you think it's compatible with monarchy?"

LineNo: 10204918,

Vina Toras: Do you think that's why the uprisi...
en


"Do you think that's why the uprising in Rizia failed? Because workers weren't the ones leading the charge?"

LineNo: 10205044,

Vina Toras: You wouldn't allow me onto the cou...
en


"You wouldn't allow me onto the council. There are only so many balls I can attend. What else am I supposed to do?"

LineNo: 10205162,

Vina Toras: Endlessly dull, you mean. Will you...
en


"Endlessly dull, you mean. Will you please give me my book back?"

LineNo: 10205272,

Narrator: Vina gave me a conspiratorial nod.
en


Vina gave me a conspiratorial nod.

LineNo: 10205374,

Vina Toras: I won't.
en


"I won't."

LineNo: 10205476,

Player_Romus: That name sounds familiar.
en


"That name sounds familiar."

LineNo: 10205578,

Vina Toras: This was one of his first tracts....
en


"This was one of his first tracts. He wrote it right before changing his name to Malenyev."

LineNo: 10205680,

Player_Romus: And? Are you learning anything int...
en


"And? Are you learning anything interesting?"

LineNo: 10205782,

Vina Toras: They thought that was what they wa...
en


"They thought that was what they wanted. Because nobody bothered to teach them otherwise."

LineNo: 10205900,

Vina Toras: And aristocrats working for their...
en


"And aristocrats working for their own gain, right? Like your kidnappers."

LineNo: 10206018,

Player_Romus: This is no way for a Toras to be c...
en


"This is no way for a Toras to be carrying on. I'm taking this book away from you."

LineNo: 10206120,

Player_Romus: I knew you'd learn more off the co...
en


"I knew you'd learn more off the council than on it. Keep it up."

LineNo: 10206222,

Estela Toras: Chin up, now. I'll see you at supp...
en


"Chin up, now. I'll see you at supper."

LineNo: 10206324,

Narrator: My mother raised her parasol and st...
en


My mother raised her parasol and strode away.

LineNo: 10206522,

Narrator: Vina stared at me in disbelief for...
en


Vina stared at me in disbelief for a moment.

LineNo: 10206720,

Vina Toras: I will. Enjoy the boring meetings.
en


"I will. Enjoy the boring meetings."

LineNo: 10206822,

Narrator: She took the book and walked away,...
en


She took the book and walked away, leaving me to my own thoughts. Before I knew it, it was time for the council meeting.

LineNo: 10207020,

Player_Romus: Where did you find this?
en


"Where did you find this?"

LineNo: 10207122,

Vina Toras: It was just lying around in the li...
en


"It was just lying around in the library. One of his supporters must have had it translated into Rizian."

LineNo: 10207224,

Vina Toras: Of course, he wrote this right bef...
en


"Of course, he wrote this right before he changed his name to Malenyev."

LineNo: 10207326,

Player_Romus: Malenyev? What happened to Queen L...
en


"Malenyev? What happened to Queen Lyza?"

LineNo: 10207428,

Vina Toras: I've read all her writings already...
en


"I've read all her writings already. And this one applies to our modern era far more."

LineNo: 10207626,

Narrator: Vina stared at me in disbelief for...
en


Vina stared at me in disbelief for a second, then smiled.

LineNo: 10207728,

Player_Romus: No. Find another use of your time.
en


"No. Find another use of your time."

LineNo: 10207830,

Player_Romus: It's overwhelming at times. But I...
en


"It's overwhelming at times. But I trust the council to help me decide."

LineNo: 10207932,

Narrator: She lowered the black lace parasol...
en


She lowered the black lace parasol she was holding and linked her arm through mine.

LineNo: 10208034,

Narrator: She reached into her handbag and pu...
en


She reached into her handbag and pulled out a slim paperback. On its cover were the words "Ce Faximi", or "What Are We To Do?" in Rizian.

LineNo: 10208414,

Vina Toras: I have plenty. But I'll figure the...
en


"I have plenty. But I'll figure them out on my own time."

LineNo: 10208516,

Vina Toras: All of this council stuff is old h...
en


"All of this council stuff is old hat for you, isn't it? You've even served with some of the same people before."

LineNo: 10208642,

Estela Toras: One more thing, darling...
en


"One more thing, darling..."

LineNo: 10208744,

Narrator: I took a closer look at the cover....
en


I took a closer look at the cover. Beneath the title were the words, "A Collection of Proposals by L. Chavatangakwunua."

LineNo: 10209148,

Estela Toras: I found this in Vina's room after...
en


"I found this in Vina's room after she went to lunch. Her way of rebelling against you for not letting her on the council, I assume."

LineNo: 10209250,

Player_Romus: Is this what I think it is?.
en


"Is this what I think it is?."

LineNo: 10209352,

Estela Toras: She was too quiet. I worried she w...
en


"She was too quiet. I worried she was up to something."

LineNo: 10209454,

Player_Romus: I'm the king. Every decision I mak...
en


"I'm the king. Every decision I make is the right decision."

LineNo: 10209556,

Player_Romus: Chava-what?
en


"Chava-what?"

LineNo: 10209658,

Player_Romus: What were you doing snooping aroun...
en


"What were you doing snooping around my daughter's room?"

LineNo: 10209760,

Player_Romus: She's been reading this? Interesti...
en


"She's been reading this? Interesting."

LineNo: 10209862,

Estela Toras: I remember hearing that name a lon...
en


"I remember hearing that name a long time ago. Before he changed it to Malenyev."

LineNo: 10209988,

Vina Toras: Oh! Hello, Father.
en


"Oh! Hello, Father."

LineNo: 10210106,

Vina Toras: This must be overwhelming for you...
en


"This must be overwhelming for you as well. So many decisions to make."

LineNo: 10210232,

Player_Romus: A long time ago. Frankly, they sho...
en


"A long time ago. Frankly, they should have retired by now."

LineNo: 10210334,

Vina Toras: Any good monarch listens to the wi...
en


"Any good monarch listens to the will of the public. Queen Lyza always said that."

LineNo: 10210460,

Player_Romus: Queen Lyza wasn't a saint. She had...
en


"Queen Lyza wasn't a saint. She had her flaws."

LineNo: 10210658,

Vina Toras: By the time she was my age, she'd...
en


"By the time she was my age, she'd already been queen for a year. Imagine!"

LineNo: 10210760,

Player_Romus: Yes, it's easy enough. I'm the kin...
en


"Yes, it's easy enough. I'm the king. What I say goes."

LineNo: 10210862,

Player_Romus: Don't you worry about me. Focus on...
en


"Don't you worry about me. Focus on keeping your own head above water."

LineNo: 10210964,

Vina Toras: I know. But it's still an inspirin...
en


"I know. But it's still an inspiring legacy to live up to."

LineNo: 10211066,

Player_Romus: It's different now that I'm the on...
en


"It's different now that I'm the one in charge."

LineNo: 10211168,

Player_Romus: Of course I will. They're the best...
en


"Of course I will. They're the best hope we have for giving Rizians an actual voice."

LineNo: 10211270,

Player_Romus: Wise words from a wise woman.
en


"Wise words from a wise woman."

LineNo: 10211372,

Player_Romus: I was naive back then. Now I don't...
en


"I was naive back then. Now I don't know whom I can trust."

LineNo: 10211474,

Vina Toras: Lyza acted, too.
en


"Lyza acted, too."

LineNo: 10211576,

Vina Toras: You can always trust me, Father.
en


"You can always trust me, Father."

LineNo: 10211678,

Vina Toras: Ms. Werner and Mr. Esquibel may be...
en


"Ms. Werner and Mr. Esquibel may be old, but what they were saying made a lot of sense to me."

LineNo: 10211780,

Player_Romus: A good monarch listens. A great mo...
en


"A good monarch listens. A great monarch acts."

LineNo: 10211882,

Player_Romus: And if the will of the public is f...
en


"And if the will of the public is for there to be no monarch at all? What then?"

LineNo: 10211984,

Vina Toras: If you rule as well as she did, th...
en


"If you rule as well as she did, that won't ever become a problem."

LineNo: 10212086,

Player_Romus: Lead the way, Your Highness.
en


"Lead the way, Your Highness."

LineNo: 10212188,

Vina Toras: I will. I've been taking notes.
en


"I will. I've been taking notes."

LineNo: 10212290,

Player_Romus: I'm not against the opposition bec...
en


"I'm not against the opposition because of House Sazon. I'm against it because it's the opposition."

LineNo: 10212392,

Player_Romus: I'll take their opinions into cons...
en


"I'll take their opinions into consideration. But I'm the one with the final say."

LineNo: 10212494,

Player_Romus: I might, but I don't want anything...
en


"I might, but I don't want anything to do with your friend Mr. Sazon."

LineNo: 10212596,

Vina Toras: Why do you have it out for House S...
en


"Why do you have it out for House Sazon? Just because one duke plotted against the king doesn't mean the whole family is evil."

LineNo: 10212722,

Player_Romus: Lucas put a taint on his entire ho...
en


"Lucas put a taint on his entire house. I won't discuss this further."

LineNo: 10212824,

Player_Romus: It's not all of the Sazons. Manus...
en


"It's not all of the Sazons. Manus in particular strikes me as suspicious."

LineNo: 10212926,

Vina Toras: Suspicious? He wants to work with...
en


"Suspicious? He wants to work with you. Why not at least hear what he has to say?"

LineNo: 10213028,

Vina Toras: Oh. Right.
en


"Oh. Right."

LineNo: 10213130,

Vina Toras: Okay, Father.
en


"Okay, Father."

LineNo: 10213232,

Vina Toras: What do you think of the House of...
en


"What do you think of the House of Delegates? Will you go talk to them?"

LineNo: 10213358,

Player_Romus: The only reason I would do that is...
en


"The only reason I would do that is to find out the opposition's weaknesses."

LineNo: 10213556,

Player_Romus: The Sazons have never truly been a...
en


"The Sazons have never truly been a royal house. Their ancestor had no claim to the throne."

LineNo: 10213658,

Narrator: A clock chimed in the distance. It...
en


A clock chimed in the distance. It was time for the meeting.

LineNo: 10213768,

Vina Toras: I can't imagine how it feels to ho...
en


"I can't imagine how it feels to hold all that power."

LineNo: 10213870,

Player_Romus: Enough chit-chat. Let's go.
en


"Enough chit-chat. Let's go."

LineNo: 10213972,

Vina Toras: The royal heir doesn't always have...
en


"The royal heir doesn't always have to be the king's son. Sometimes there are special circumstances."

LineNo: 10214074,

Vina Toras: Um... not really. A society ruled...
en


"Um... not really. A society ruled by a king is the embodiment of everything Malenyevists hate."

LineNo: 10214176,

Vina Toras: But it's useful to know how they t...
en


"But it's useful to know how they think, isn't it?"

LineNo: 10214278,

Vina Toras: I mean... of course it's all rubbi...
en


"I mean... of course it's all rubbish. But it does make one think."

LineNo: 10214380,

Vina Toras: The student and workers' movement...
en


"The student and workers' movement was more aligned with Malenyevism, but the nobles who rebelled were in favor of Arcasian democracy."

LineNo: 10214698,

Estela Toras: And reading Malenyevist tracts is...
en


"And reading Malenyevist tracts is definitely 'something'."

LineNo: 10214824,

Estela Toras: That's an underreaction, wouldn't...
en


"That's an underreaction, wouldn't you say? Malenyevist tracts belong in an incinerator, not your daughter's bedroom."

LineNo: 10214942,

Estela Toras: I can see why he changed it to 'Ma...
en


"I can see why he changed it to 'Malenyev', That's one unholy mass of letters."

LineNo: 10215068,

Player_Romus: There were Malenyevists involved i...
en


"There were Malenyevists involved in the '26 uprising, weren't there? It could be useful to learn how the enemy thinks."

LineNo: 10215170,

Player_Romus: You're right, Mother. I'm sure it'...
en


"You're right, Mother. I'm sure it's pure garbage."

LineNo: 10215272,

Player_Romus: Vina's a smart girl. She wouldn't...
en


"Vina's a smart girl. She wouldn't be reading this if there weren't value in it."

LineNo: 10215374,

Estela Toras: That's what I'm worried about, dea...
en


"That's what I'm worried about, dear."

LineNo: 10215476,

Player_Romus: I see. Well, better this than Arca...
en


"I see. Well, better this than Arcasian garbage."

LineNo: 10215674,

Player_Romus: The man had some good ideas. Maybe...
en


"The man had some good ideas. Maybe his vision of a more egalitarian society isn't entirely incompatible with monarchy."

LineNo: 10215776,

Estela Toras: My dear, I'm no scholar, but I do...
en


"My dear, I'm no scholar, but I do know there's a direct correlation between this fellow's line of thinking and royal beheadings."

LineNo: 10215878,

Estela Toras: The workers and students were insp...
en


"The workers and students were inspired by Malenyevism. The nobles who got involved were pushing for Arcasian-style democracy."

LineNo: 10215980,

Estela Toras: I'm no scholar myself. But I do kn...
en


"I'm no scholar myself. But I do know the former leads to more royal beheadings than the latter."

LineNo: 10216082,

Estela Toras: It's more than that, dear. Garbage...
en


"It's more than that, dear. Garbage won't cut off your head in the middle of the night."

LineNo: 10216184,

Estela Toras: So what should I do with the book?
en


"So what should I do with the book?"

LineNo: 10216294,

Estela Toras: My dear, I'm no scholar, but I do...
en


"My dear, I'm no scholar, but I do know there's a direct correlation between this fellow's line of thinking and royal beheadings."

LineNo: 10216396,

Estela Toras: They're like cannons at that age....
en


"They're like cannons at that age. You've got to mind the direction they're pointed in, or there'll be hell to pay when they go off."

LineNo: 10216498,

Estela Toras: Very well. But I do suggest having...
en


"Very well. But I do suggest having a chat with her about this."

LineNo: 10216600,

Narrator: She put the book back in her purse.
en


She put the book back in her purse.

LineNo: 10216798,

Player_Romus: Put it back where you found it. Vi...
en


"Put it back where you found it. Vina's allowed to read what she wants in her free time."

LineNo: 10216900,
